                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-262-off1406 t18250915-262-victim1330"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>JOHN TILLEY. On the 11th of July, between four and five o'clock, I was in <placeName id="t18250915-262-crimeloc1408">Arlington-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-262-crimeloc1408" type="placeName" value="Arlington-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-262-crimeloc1408" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-262-off1406 t18250915-262-crimeloc1408"></join> - I felt a pulling behind me, turned round, and saw the prisoner, and two others, near me; but the prisoner was nearest. I took hold of him, and found my handkerchief in his hand - he was in the act of giving it to another boy.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I saw two young men following this gentleman - his handkerchief was half out of his pocket; I saw them in the act of picking his pocket; I called out to the gentleman, and they threw the handkerchief down - the gentleman turned round and took me.</p>
               <p>JOHN TILLEY re-examined. Q. Did he say any thing of this at the time? A. No, but when I took him to the watch-house, he begged forgiveness, it being his first offence.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18250915-262-verdict1409" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18250915-262-verdict1409" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 14.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18250915-262-punish1410" type="punishmentDescription">
